### isDeInterleaveMask() {#a1197fc4e7554381767b15551de4f9334}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isDeInterleaveMask (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; int &gt; Mask, unsigned &amp; Factor, unsigned &amp; Index, unsigned MaxFactor, unsigned NumLoadElements)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/check">Check</a> if the mask is a DE-interleave mask for an interleaved load.

E.g. DE-interleave masks (Factor = 2) could be: &lt;0, 2, 4, 6&gt; (mask of index 0 to extract even elements) &lt;1, 3, 5, 7&gt; (mask of index 1 to extract odd elements)

Definition at line <a href="#l00208">208</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/interleavedaccesspass-cpp">InterleavedAccessPass.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### isReInterleaveMask() {#aa5abbc18f35b5384a55bfd244064493d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isReInterleaveMask (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/shufflevectorinst">ShuffleVectorInst</a> &#42; SVI, unsigned &amp; Factor, unsigned MaxFactor)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/check">Check</a> if the mask can be used in an interleaved store.

It checks for a more general pattern than the RE-interleave mask. I.e. &lt;x, y, ... z, x+1, y+1, ...z+1, x+2, y+2, ...z+2, ...&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4): &lt;4, 32, 5, 33, 6, 34, 7, 35&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 3 (LaneLen=4): &lt;4, 32, 16, 5, 33, 17, 6, 34, 18, 7, 35, 19&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 4 (LaneLen=2): &lt;8, 2, 12, 4, 9, 3, 13, 5&gt;

The particular case of an RE-interleave mask is: I.e. &lt;0, LaneLen, ... , LaneLen&#42;(Factor - 1), 1, LaneLen + 1, ...&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4): &lt;0, 4, 1, 5, 2, 6, 3, 7&gt;

Definition at line <a href="#l00237">237</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/interleavedaccesspass-cpp">InterleavedAccessPass.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

<Link id="l00006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="6"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="7"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="8"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This file implements the Interleaved Access pass, which identifies</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// interleaved memory accesses and transforms them into target specific</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intrinsics.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// An interleaved load reads data from memory into several vectors, with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// DE-interleaving the data on a factor. An interleaved store writes several</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// vectors to memory with RE-interleaving the data on a factor.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// As interleaved accesses are difficult to identified in CodeGen (mainly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// because the VECTOR&#95;SHUFFLE DAG node is quite different from the shufflevector</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// IR), we identify and transform them to intrinsics in this pass so the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intrinsics can be easily matched into target specific instructions later in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// CodeGen.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// E.g. An interleaved load (Factor = 2):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        %wide.vec = load &lt;8 x i32&gt;, &lt;8 x i32&gt;&#42; %ptr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        %v0 = shuffle &lt;8 x i32&gt; %wide.vec, &lt;8 x i32&gt; poison, &lt;0, 2, 4, 6&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        %v1 = shuffle &lt;8 x i32&gt; %wide.vec, &lt;8 x i32&gt; poison, &lt;1, 3, 5, 7&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It could be transformed into a ld2 intrinsic in AArch64 backend or a vld2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intrinsic in ARM backend.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In X86, this can be further optimized into a set of target</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// specific loads followed by an optimized sequence of shuffles.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// E.g. An interleaved store (Factor = 3):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        %i.vec = shuffle &lt;8 x i32&gt; %v0, &lt;8 x i32&gt; %v1,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                                    &lt;0, 4, 8, 1, 5, 9, 2, 6, 10, 3, 7, 11&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        store &lt;12 x i32&gt; %i.vec, &lt;12 x i32&gt;&#42; %ptr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It could be transformed into a st3 intrinsic in AArch64 backend or a vst3</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intrinsic in ARM backend.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Similarly, a set of interleaved stores can be transformed into an optimized</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sequence of shuffles followed by a set of target specific stores for X86.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#include &quot;<a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/arrayref-h">llvm/ADT/ArrayRef.h</a>&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#include &quot;<a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/densemap-h">llvm/ADT/DenseMap.h</a>&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#include &quot;<a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/setvector-h">llvm/ADT/SetVector.h</a>&quot;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For an (de)interleave tree like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A   C B   D</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   |&#95;&#95;&#95;| |&#95;&#95;&#95;|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00486" /><CodeLine lineNumber="486"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     |&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;|</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00487" /><CodeLine lineNumber="487"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00488" /><CodeLine lineNumber="488"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     A B C D</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00489" /><CodeLine lineNumber="489"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00490" /><CodeLine lineNumber="490"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  We will get ABCD at the end while the leaf operands/results</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00491" /><CodeLine lineNumber="491"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  are ACBD, which are also what we initially collected in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00492" /><CodeLine lineNumber="492"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  getVectorInterleaveFactor / getVectorDeinterleaveFactor. But TLI</span></CodeLine>
